$interpreted: Li-Hwa: (Elio, Juan-Yun and all them went to the Alliance Hall. I doubt they'll be back any time soon.)
Li-Hwa: There's no one around., you can come out.
Bewitcher: L—Li-Hwa... You're back...
Li-Hwa: Haven't I told you all not to come out of the manor? What if you were caught!?
Li-Hwa: All those bewitched... did you do that?
Yokai: I'm sorry, but... Soohyeon...
Li-Hwa: Soohyeon? What's wrong?
Bewitcher: You were away in the Kingdom of the Sun for so long, and we ran out of medicine...
Bewitcher: Soohyeon's been getting it for us in the meantime, but she hasn't come back yet today. Everyone's worried, so I came out to look...
Li-Hwa: (That Soohyeon, she's definitely pretending to be a human to get meds... But...)
Alliance Soldier: Found you, bewitcher!
Alliance Soldier: You... You're Li-Hwa of the Jellyfish Tribe, aren't you?
Li-Hwa: Eh? You know me?
Alliance Soldier: Of course, you're famous! You should step back, though, that's a bewitcher! You wouldn't want to touch him!
Alliance Soldier: He's been ambushing busy medicine markets. He's bewitched quite a large number of people already!
Bewitcher: I didn't mean to... Once they discovered I was a bewitcher, they chased after me. I was just trying to escape, not hurt anyone...
Alliance Soldier: Enough with the excuses! You can apologize to the ones you've killed after you're dead!
Li-Hwa: Is that so? He did that all by himself?
Alliance Soldier: That's right, but... Weird, shouldn't a bunch of bewitched be following him?
Li-Hwa: Don't worry, I'll bring him back to where he belongs.
Li-Hwa: After I deal with you.
Alliance Soldier: Empress... you... why...?
Li-Hwa: I'm sorry, I understand your concern, but you should really treat the cause, not the symptoms.
Alliance Soldier: Ugh... what did you just give me?
Li-Hwa: It'll make you sleep. It'll also give you a bit of amnesia.
Alliance Soldier: You—
Li-Hwa: Alright, he's asleep.
Bewitcher: I'm sorry for involving you in this. You were just trying to help...
Li-Hwa: It's too dangerous outside of the manor. How come you came out alone?
Bewitcher: I'm older than the others. They're all just kids...
Li-Hwa: That's no reason to put yourself in danger. I'm much older than all of you combined, you know.
Bewitcher: But, you're a jellyfish. You're basically immortal!
Li-Hwa: Poor thing...
Bewitcher: You should step back a bit. You wouldn't want to touch me.
Li-Hwa: It must be tough, huh?
Li-Hwa: You touch anyone, and they get bewitched and die.
Li-Hwa: Everyone is scared of you, hates you, wants you gone. And you can't deny it, because it really is all your fault.
Bewitcher: ......
Li-Hwa: It must be so difficult, isn't it?
Bewitcher: ...Yes, more than you could imagine.
Li-Hwa: Then what keeps you going? Why don't you just end it?
Bewitcher: ...Because of what you told us. You said you would find a way to turn us back to normal, and to wait for you...
Li-Hwa: That's right, I did... And if we can't cure it at the root, more and more people will die.
Li-Hwa: I hate this just as much as you do. I want this to stop.
Bewitcher: Li-Hwa...
Li-Hwa: It's not just your problem or my problem. This affects all of the east.
Li-Hwa: Those up in the Alliance Hall don't care. They pretend this curse doesn't exist. I'm not the same—I see it and I want it gone.
Bewitcher: ...I know...
Li-Hwa: Good. We need to work together on this.
Li-Hwa: So until I figure this out, please just wait for me in the manor.
Bewitcher: Ugh, do we have to take that same medicine again? It was so bitter...
Li-Hwa: Nope, this one's twice as bitter.
Bewitcher: What!?
Li-Hwa: I'll deal with Soohyeon and this soldier. You get back to Pearl Manor and let the others know everything is okay.
Bewitcher: Okay... Thank you, Li-Hwa.
Li-Hwa: (I'm sorry... everyone is suffering. Please, wait just a little longer. I'll find a cure.)
Soohyeon: (First the honey badgers, then fugitives... It wasn't easy getting out of the Alliance Hall.)
Soohyeon: (Everyone at Pearl Manor has been waiting for so long. I've got to get back there!)
Tica: Miss~ Li~ Hwaaa~ Where areeee youuu~?
Elio: Hey, quiet! What the heck are you doing!?
Tica: She's well-known, isn't she? I figure if I yell her name, someone will come help out.
Elio: Umm... Can't you see we're in the middle of nowhere? There's no one around.
Tica: Oh yeah... I guess you're right.
Elio: Hmm... We should really have Pang and Jia-Shen come help.
Tica: No way! Those two haven't seen each other in a long time. And didn't you hear what Comrade Pang said to us when we met up?
Tica: He's got to get into a lot of fights. He's got to be able to rest in between to keep his strength!
Elio: He's part of the Martial Arts Tournament, he's not just 'getting into fights'. You sure you heard him correctly?
Tica: Whatever, they're still fights to me. The important thing is that Li-Hwa is missing. We've got to find her!
Tica: Li~ Hwaaaa~ Where aaare youuu~~~?
Elio: Seems like you're pretty 'whatever' about everything, aren't you...
Soohyeon: Excuse me... you're looking for Li-Hwa?
Elio: It actually worked...
Soohyeon: Sorry, but I heard your conversation. Did Li-Hwa come back from the Kingdom of the Sun?
Elio: She did. We were on the same boat... Are you a human, too?
Tica: We're looking for Li-Hwa, she's gone missing! Do you know where she lives?
Soohyeon: I do, but... Can I ask why you're looking for her? How do you know her?
Tica: We're students at the Rune Academy.
Tica: Miss Li-Hwa told us she wanted to discuss runes and qi with us, so we came to the east.
Soohyeon: (They call her Miss Li-Hwa... I guess that means they really do know her.)
Soohyeon: Okay... Li-Hwa is the maiden of Seamoon Manor, so I'll bring you all down there.
Tica: Great~~ Let's go, Elio!
Elio: Hold on!
Tica: What's wrong? You look all serious...
Elio: Even beasts don't know about this place. What's a human doing wandering around here? And one that just happens to know Li-Hwa so well?
Soohyeon: Well, I was just in the area...
Elio: And you want us to come with you? Who are you?
Soohyeon: ......
Tica: Oh, Elio! You're so mean!
Elio: Tica, don't interrupt!
Tica: ...Okay...
Soohyeon: I am—
Li-Hwa: She's not a human.
Elio: Miss Li-Hwa!?
Soohyeon: Li-Hwa! You're back!
Li-Hwa: I've been looking for you. Thanks for taking care of Pearl Manor while I was gone.
Tica: Well, they do seem to know each other. But... Li-Hwa, what do you mean she's not human?
Elio: Yeah, can you explain?
Li-Hwa: Ah, well, this just happens to be why I invited you both here in the first place.
Li-Hwa: But it's not safe to talk here. Let's get back to the manor.
Li-Hwa: This way.
